OL,3,GNorthern Ireland
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FDry and bright in the morning
OL,6,Fafter a chilly start. Becoming warm
OL,7,Fagain by day, with sunshine turning
OL,8,Fhazy as it becomes cloudier at times
OL,9,Flater with some drizzle possible,
OL,10,Flight winds.
OL,11,
OL,12,CTonight:FA dry evening with sunny
OL,13,Fspells, perhaps still cloudy around
OL,14,Fwestern areas. Cloud developing later
OL,15,Fin the night with a few spots of rain
OL,16,Fpossible.
OL,17,
OL,18,CSunday:FCloudy but mainly dry in the
OL,19,Fmorning, a few afternoon showers
OL,20,Fdeveloping and these turning sharp in
OL,21,Fplaces.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
